Great progress! The E2E test is now working for the first 2 tests (stable event, degraded → healing → restored). The backup entry test is failing — the healer is writing to `REAL_REGISTRY` (the real config/providers.json) but the backup entry isn't appearing.

The issue might be that the healer's SimulatedAgentSession reads/writes to a hardcoded path. Let me check what path it uses:

```ts
const REGISTRY_PATH = resolve(import.meta.dir, "../../../", "config", "providers.json");
```

`import.meta.dir` for `packages/healer/src/agent.ts` would be something like `C:/Users/lipey/Code/Resilynx/packages/healer/src`. Going up 3 levels: `C:/Users/lipey/Code/Resilynx`. So the path would be `C:/Users/lipey/Code/Resilynx/config/providers.json`.

And my `REAL_REGISTRY` is computed as:
```ts
const REAL_REGISTRY = resolve(import.meta.dir, "../../../config/providers.json");
```

Where `import.meta.dir` is `apps/backend/src` for the test file. Going up 3 levels: `C:/Users/lipey/Code/Resilynx`. So `REAL_REGISTRY` = `C:/Users/lipey/Code/Resilynx/config/providers.json`. Same path!

So the healer should be writing to it. But the backup isn't appearing. Let me debug.

The issue might be that the healer writes to the file, but the `restored` event fires before the file is fully written. Or the healer might not be writing because it can't find the provider or the error log.

Let me look at the SimulatedAgentSession more carefully:

```ts
async run(prompt: string, callbacks: AgentCallbacks): Promise<void> {
    callbacks.onTurnStart("analysing");
    const providerId = this.extractProviderId(prompt);
    const errorLog = this.extractErrorLog(prompt);
    if (!providerId && !errorLog) {
      callbacks.onTurnEnd();
      return;
    }
    callbacks.onTurnStart("reading-registry");
    const entries: ProviderRegistryEntry[] = this.readRegistry();
    const failedIndex = entries.findIndex((e) => e.id === providerId);
    if (failedIndex === -1) {
      callbacks.onTurnEnd();
      return;
    }
    const failedEntry = entries[failedIndex];
    if (failedEntry.authMode === "zeroxyz") {
      callbacks.onTurnEnd();
      return;
    }
    callbacks.onTurnStart("discovering-backup");
    const backup = this.simulateZeroXyzDiscovery(failedEntry);
    if (entries.some((entry) => entry.id === backup.id)) {
      callbacks.onTurnEnd();
      return;
    }
    callbacks.onTurnStart("patching-registry");
    backup.priority = failedEntry.priority + 1;
    backup.authMode = "zeroxyz";
    entries.push(backup);
    this.writeRegistry(entries);
    callbacks.onTurnEnd();
  }
```

And `extractProviderId`:
```ts
private extractProviderId(prompt: string): string | undefined {
    const m = prompt.match(/Provider ID:\s*(\S+)/);
    return m?.[1];
}
```

And `extractErrorLog`:
```ts
private extractErrorLog(prompt: string): string | undefined {
    const m = prompt.match(/Error Log:\s*(.+)/);
    return m?.[1];
}
```

The prompt format from `buildAgentPrompt`:
```ts
function buildAgentPrompt(failure: FailureEvent): string {
  return [
    "You are the Resilynx Healing Orchestrator (Pi Agent).",
    ...
    `Provider ID: ${failure.providerId}`,
    `Error Log: ${failure.errorLog}`,
    ...
  ].join("\n");
